1
00:00:45,545 --> 00:00:48,506
{\an8}Are you saying that she will make
chaos here in the Philippines?

2
00:00:48,590 --> 00:00:53,428
{\an8}Not just in the Philippines,
but in the whole world.

3
00:01:11,112 --> 00:01:13,573
{\an8}It could be a nuclear bomb
or chemical bomb,

4
00:01:13,656 --> 00:01:17,660
{\an8}it's just a very, very powerful weapon.

5
00:01:51,277 --> 00:01:52,654
{\an8}So that's it?

6
00:01:53,321 --> 00:01:54,989
{\an8}Chiara has been excommunicated?

7
00:01:55,740 --> 00:01:57,617
{\an8}She's no longer family, that's it?

8
00:01:57,700 --> 00:01:58,952
{\an8}You did nothing?

9
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:02,956
{\an8}You let Isabella make a decision
for our daughter?

10
00:02:08,503 --> 00:02:10,755
{\an8}It's always about the Moraviano!

11
00:02:11,339 --> 00:02:12,715
{\an8}You're Chiara's father.

12
00:02:13,258 --> 00:02:15,760
{\an8}Okay? We need to protect our daughter.

13
00:02:15,844 --> 00:02:17,303
{\an8}Believe me.

14
00:02:19,389 --> 00:02:22,725
{\an8}And we are powerless
against La Morte Bianca.

15
00:02:28,690 --> 00:02:30,608
{\an8}Wherever she may be right now.

16
00:02:42,370 --> 00:02:47,208
{\an8}Let's think about our survival first,
before our daughter.

17
00:02:55,008 --> 00:02:56,634
{\an8}You're pretty good at escaping.

18
00:02:56,718 --> 00:02:58,720
{\an8}Of course, I learned from you.

19
00:02:59,679 --> 00:03:01,556
{\an8}- From me, really?
- Yes.

20
00:03:01,639 --> 00:03:03,975
{\an8}Didn't you use to sneak out of school?

21
00:03:04,475 --> 00:03:07,228
{\an8}You were always climbing walls.

22
00:03:07,312 --> 00:03:08,730
{\an8}Huh? No way!

23
00:03:08,813 --> 00:03:11,065
{\an8}Do I look like someone who cuts classes?

24
00:03:11,149 --> 00:03:12,442
{\an8}I never cut class.

25
00:03:13,776 --> 00:03:16,988
{\an8}Wow, look at Mr. Pinagpala!

26
00:03:19,824 --> 00:03:21,618
{\an8}Of course, who else?

27
00:03:21,701 --> 00:03:22,911
{\an8}I've always been a good boy.

28
00:03:28,541 --> 00:03:31,878
{\an8}You know, sweetheart,
this is real freedom.

29
00:03:31,961 --> 00:03:35,757
{\an8}Just eating ice cream
while walking around.

30
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:39,219
{\an8}Then talking about our past.

31
00:03:39,302 --> 00:03:40,220
{\an8}You know?

32
00:03:40,303 --> 00:03:42,513
{\an8}Reminiscing. Like this.

33
00:03:47,143 --> 00:03:49,520
{\an8}It's definitely easier to escape.

34
00:03:49,604 --> 00:03:51,606
{\an8}When no one is chasing you.

35
00:03:52,774 --> 00:03:54,192
And when no one says,

36
00:03:55,443 --> 00:03:57,403
"What do you think you're doing?"

37
00:03:58,821 --> 00:04:01,157
Or when no one says,

38
00:04:01,824 --> 00:04:04,786
"Just a reminder,
don't do anything stupid."

39
00:04:04,869 --> 00:04:06,037
Wow!

40
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:08,289
You sound exactly like Agent Alex!

41
00:04:10,041 --> 00:04:12,961
You know, I think
that Ben guy is already awake.

42
00:04:13,044 --> 00:04:16,214
And he probably told Agent Alex
about what we did.

43
00:04:16,297 --> 00:04:19,801
So I'm sure that any minute now,
their vehicle will arrive,

44
00:04:19,884 --> 00:04:21,552
and stop right in front of us.

45
00:04:21,636 --> 00:04:23,930
And Sianong will be the first to speak.

46
00:04:24,806 --> 00:04:27,308
"Would you rather be locked up in jail?"

47
00:04:27,392 --> 00:04:28,226
"We can arrange that."

48
00:04:28,810 --> 00:04:29,936
Then Agent Alex will say,

49
00:04:31,062 --> 00:04:32,730
"Do you think this is funny?"

50
00:04:32,814 --> 00:04:34,232
"You're ruining everything!"

51
00:04:45,118 --> 00:04:47,829
Would you rather be locked up in jail?

52
00:04:47,912 --> 00:04:48,746
We can arrange that!

53
00:04:54,627 --> 00:04:55,837
See?

54
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:57,088
I told you!

55
00:05:04,345 --> 00:05:07,015
We just went out for ice cream.
There wasn't any at the safe house.

56
00:05:07,098 --> 00:05:08,558
That's why we went out.

57
00:05:08,641 --> 00:05:09,684
Yes.

58
00:05:13,563 --> 00:05:17,608
Do you realize that because of this,
the agency will trust you even less?

59
00:05:17,692 --> 00:05:19,986
We're sorry, we were already heading back.

60
00:05:20,069 --> 00:05:22,322
You just got here first
because you have a vehicle.

61
00:05:22,989 --> 00:05:23,823
Come on, let's go.

62
00:05:23,906 --> 00:05:25,074
- Let's go back together.
- Get in.

63
00:05:48,097 --> 00:05:49,223
Yay!

64
00:05:50,933 --> 00:05:52,185
Are you making deliveries?

65
00:05:53,269 --> 00:05:54,270
I'll come with you.

66
00:05:54,353 --> 00:05:55,855
There's only one motorcycle.

67
00:05:55,938 --> 00:05:57,815
That's our delivery vehicle.

68
00:05:57,899 --> 00:05:59,233
So what's the problem?

69
00:05:59,317 --> 00:06:00,693
I'll just ride with you.

70
00:06:00,777 --> 00:06:03,529
Huh? No, just stay here.

71
00:06:03,613 --> 00:06:05,740
Come on, this isn't new to you.

72
00:06:05,823 --> 00:06:09,243
You used to ride with me before,
now it's my turn to ride with you.

73
00:06:09,327 --> 00:06:10,411
Give and take, right?

74
00:06:10,495 --> 00:06:12,121
Come on already!

75
00:06:12,205 --> 00:06:14,082
If we're riding together, let's do it.

76
00:06:14,165 --> 00:06:15,333
Get going already,

77
00:06:15,416 --> 00:06:17,502
so the tortas will still be warm
when they're delivered.

78
00:06:17,585 --> 00:06:18,419
Hurry up.

79
00:06:21,589 --> 00:06:22,590
Come with us.

80
00:06:22,673 --> 00:06:24,634
- Be careful.
- I'm definitely coming.

81
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:27,512
Come on, they're waiting for those.

82
00:06:28,012 --> 00:06:29,680
- Hey Angelito, take care of her.
- Wait, wait.

83
00:06:29,764 --> 00:06:30,598
Ouch.

84
00:06:30,681 --> 00:06:32,266
There!

85
00:06:32,350 --> 00:06:34,143
- Take care.
- Are you ready?

86
00:06:34,227 --> 00:06:36,229
- I'm ready.
- Okay.

87
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:38,689
Hold on tight!

88
00:06:38,773 --> 00:06:39,607
Take care.

89
00:06:39,690 --> 00:06:42,026
‪PINAGPALA
‪SPECIAL BAKESHOP

90
00:06:44,028 --> 00:06:47,323
Tess, you can come out now!

91
00:06:51,119 --> 00:06:51,828
Hey.

92
00:06:51,911 --> 00:06:53,955
Are you sure they're gone?

93
00:06:54,038 --> 00:06:54,914
Absolutely sure.

94
00:06:56,290 --> 00:06:57,291
I knew it!

95
00:06:57,375 --> 00:06:58,835
You left on purpose earlier, didn't you?

96
00:06:58,918 --> 00:07:02,338
Pretending you had to prepare lunch.
What an excuse.

97
00:07:02,421 --> 00:07:04,465
Well, of course. If I stayed by the oven,

98
00:07:04,549 --> 00:07:06,843
how would they ever get some alone time?

99
00:07:06,926 --> 00:07:08,803
I don't know with these kids.

100
00:07:08,886 --> 00:07:11,431
They even have to keep
their relationship hidden from the public.

101
00:07:11,514 --> 00:07:12,849
Anyway, let me change the subject.

102
00:07:12,932 --> 00:07:16,727
Is it true we have an order of 100 today?

103
00:07:16,811 --> 00:07:18,563
No, Tess. It's only around 30.

104
00:07:18,646 --> 00:07:22,233
I was just teasing the kids.
The order of 100 is tomorrow.

105
00:07:22,316 --> 00:07:24,861
I just wanted to see them
work under pressure.

106
00:07:26,904 --> 00:07:28,531
So how many
are we really delivering today?

107
00:07:28,614 --> 00:07:32,326
Ten of those, and we still have
fifteen torta cakes to bake.

108
00:07:32,410 --> 00:07:33,703
There are five more in the oven.

109
00:07:33,786 --> 00:07:34,745
What are we waiting for?

110
00:07:34,829 --> 00:07:36,289
Come on, let's get to work!

111
00:07:36,372 --> 00:07:38,875
- Let's go.
- Hey, where's Angel?

112
00:07:43,838 --> 00:07:47,383
How many chances have you been given,
yet the result is always the same?

113
00:07:48,718 --> 00:07:50,887
How many times are you going
to let the force down?

114
00:07:50,970 --> 00:07:51,804
Huh?

115
00:07:52,722 --> 00:07:54,307
You keep talking about
letting people down.

116
00:07:54,932 --> 00:07:56,851
Like you've never made mistakes?

117
00:07:56,934 --> 00:07:58,728
You caught them anyway.

118
00:07:59,312 --> 00:08:01,898
Besides, you did it first.

119
00:08:01,981 --> 00:08:03,983
And when did I do that?

120
00:08:05,067 --> 00:08:06,527
When you ghosted me.

121
00:08:08,488 --> 00:08:09,864
You're still stuck on that, man?

122
00:08:09,947 --> 00:08:11,657
I thought you'd moved on.

123
00:08:12,158 --> 00:08:15,328
Didn't you say you already found yourself?

124
00:08:17,038 --> 00:08:20,291
You're not the one she loves.
You're not the one she wants, okay?

125
00:08:20,374 --> 00:08:21,334
Then who?

126
00:08:22,668 --> 00:08:24,545
And she wants you?

127
00:08:39,685 --> 00:08:42,063
Do you want me to put you to sleep again?

128
00:08:49,278 --> 00:08:50,738
Thank you!

129
00:08:59,956 --> 00:09:00,915
You even have a tagline!

130
00:09:00,998 --> 00:09:02,083
Wasn't I great?

131
00:09:02,166 --> 00:09:05,753
See? I look like a legitimate
member of your bakery staff now.

132
00:09:05,836 --> 00:09:07,129
Bechay taught me that.

133
00:09:07,213 --> 00:09:09,257
- Very good.
- Really good!

134
00:09:09,340 --> 00:09:10,466
Thank you for this!

135
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:13,761
My fiancée's favorite
is your special torta.

136
00:09:13,844 --> 00:09:15,680
I'm meeting her family later.

137
00:09:16,889 --> 00:09:18,015
Can I come with you?

138
00:09:18,099 --> 00:09:19,058
What do you mean come with us?

139
00:09:19,141 --> 00:09:20,226
Are you a relative?

140
00:09:20,309 --> 00:09:22,144
You don't even know
the people who'll be there.

141
00:09:22,812 --> 00:09:24,188
I know, but…

142
00:09:24,272 --> 00:09:28,192
I just want to know
how meeting the family works.

143
00:09:28,276 --> 00:09:29,443
No.

144
00:09:29,527 --> 00:09:31,153
Sir, you're all set.

145
00:09:31,237 --> 00:09:33,197
Just give this to your fiancée and

146
00:09:33,281 --> 00:09:35,074
please ignore everything
this one just said.

147
00:09:35,157 --> 00:09:36,409
All right, thank you, Sir!

148
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:39,954
You know,

149
00:09:40,037 --> 00:09:42,456
you really love ambushing
random strangers.

150
00:09:42,540 --> 00:09:44,417
Why? I'm just curious.

151
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:45,876
What's wrong with that?

152
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:48,004
Besides, isn't that how we first met?

153
00:09:48,087 --> 00:09:49,463
When I ambushed your room.

154
00:09:56,637 --> 00:09:58,055
Hey, let me sleep.

155
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:09,817
I've already spoken to General Norberto.

156
00:10:10,401 --> 00:10:12,111
And because of what you two did,

157
00:10:12,194 --> 00:10:14,196
he's sending someone to work with you.

158
00:10:14,697 --> 00:10:15,990
Yup.

159
00:10:16,073 --> 00:10:20,411
Someone who's not addicted to
staying up late, but addicted to the gym.

160
00:10:22,038 --> 00:10:24,999
Someone who can't be
put to sleep so easily.

161
00:10:26,334 --> 00:10:27,960
Because he's tough as nails.

162
00:10:29,086 --> 00:10:30,087
Who is it?

163
00:10:44,435 --> 00:10:45,978
If you're really into burgers,

164
00:10:46,062 --> 00:10:47,438
which tastes better?

165
00:10:52,985 --> 00:10:53,819
Wrong!

166
00:10:53,903 --> 00:10:54,987
Neither is wrong!

167
00:10:55,071 --> 00:10:57,573
Because they're both delicious!

168
00:11:07,583 --> 00:11:08,417
Oh.

169
00:11:09,669 --> 00:11:11,337
Mom just sent a text.

170
00:11:11,420 --> 00:11:13,839
She said the orders are already done.

171
00:11:13,923 --> 00:11:15,966
She and Betchay finished them.

172
00:11:16,050 --> 00:11:17,259
The 100 orders?

173
00:11:17,968 --> 00:11:18,969
No.

174
00:11:19,053 --> 00:11:20,304
There were only 30!

175
00:11:20,388 --> 00:11:22,556
Bechay just made a mistake
writing it on the calendar,

176
00:11:22,640 --> 00:11:25,017
the 100 orders are actually for tomorrow.

177
00:11:25,101 --> 00:11:28,062
Oh… I thought they finished all 100.

178
00:11:28,145 --> 00:11:31,023
So, should we head back to the bakery?

179
00:11:31,941 --> 00:11:32,775
Huh?

180
00:11:32,858 --> 00:11:33,818
Oh.

181
00:11:33,901 --> 00:11:36,737
Wait, wait. I think
I just had a better idea.

182
00:11:36,821 --> 00:11:40,032
Why don't we stay here for a while?

183
00:11:40,116 --> 00:11:42,201
Show me around your town.

184
00:11:42,284 --> 00:11:44,537
Come on, let's spend some time together.

185
00:11:44,620 --> 00:11:47,915
You know, let's spend
time with each other.

186
00:11:47,998 --> 00:11:49,166
You know?

187
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,545
That's not a good idea.
Let's go back to the shop.

188
00:11:52,628 --> 00:11:53,546
Why not?

189
00:11:53,629 --> 00:11:55,923
Just look at how beautiful the weather is.

190
00:11:56,006 --> 00:11:57,341
Why don't we take a walk?

191
00:11:57,425 --> 00:11:58,676
Relax and reflect?

192
00:12:01,011 --> 00:12:07,309
<i>Because I'm starting to feel things</i>
<i>that I shouldn't be feeling.</i>

193
00:12:09,728 --> 00:12:12,356
What are these feelings
you shouldn't be feeling?

194
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,482
Huh?

195
00:12:14,733 --> 00:12:16,152
Can you read my mind?

196
00:12:16,235 --> 00:12:17,153
Huh?

197
00:12:17,236 --> 00:12:18,237
Of course not!

198
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:20,197
What am I, a mind reader?

199
00:12:20,281 --> 00:12:23,659
It's just that I've noticed you've been
holding your chest for a while now.

200
00:12:23,742 --> 00:12:25,911
So what exactly are you feeling?

201
00:12:27,997 --> 00:12:29,665
Nothing. None of your business.

202
00:12:30,458 --> 00:12:33,377
You're in love with me already,
aren't you?

203
00:12:33,461 --> 00:12:34,753
Come on, admit it.

204
00:12:34,837 --> 00:12:37,173
No way! You're so full of yourself!

205
00:12:37,256 --> 00:12:39,216
Come on, let's go home.

206
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:41,427
Get on. If you don't,
I'm leaving you behind.

207
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:43,220
All right, all right. I'm getting on.

208
00:12:43,304 --> 00:12:44,388
- Come on.
- There you go again.

209
00:12:45,764 --> 00:12:46,932
- Hold on.
- Okay.

210
00:12:47,641 --> 00:12:48,851
I got this.

211
00:12:48,934 --> 00:12:49,810
Okay.

212
00:12:55,483 --> 00:12:56,317
Hey.

213
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:57,818
What happened?

214
00:12:58,402 --> 00:12:59,403
Is it broken?

215
00:12:59,987 --> 00:13:02,448
I think the battery died.

216
00:13:03,782 --> 00:13:06,702
So that means we can't use it anymore.

217
00:13:08,037 --> 00:13:08,996
Looks like it.

218
00:13:35,356 --> 00:13:38,734
To help us with
high-stakes investigations.

219
00:13:38,817 --> 00:13:42,196
And because of your impressive
professional background,

220
00:13:42,279 --> 00:13:46,408
the state is offering to commute
the remainder of your sentence.

221
00:13:52,373 --> 00:13:53,415
In exchange for what?

222
00:14:01,590 --> 00:14:04,301
If I cooperate with you,

223
00:14:04,385 --> 00:14:08,430
can you guarantee that
the Moraviano will be brought down?

224
00:14:14,478 --> 00:14:15,479
In that case,

225
00:14:16,188 --> 00:14:20,401
if this is the only way
I can get justice for Jepoy,

226
00:14:21,777 --> 00:14:22,611
count me in.

227
00:14:36,792 --> 00:14:38,919
And he has a background
in forensic accounting.

228
00:14:40,921 --> 00:14:45,092
So we can use his expertise
to map out their financial network.

229
00:14:45,676 --> 00:14:49,221
Oh! Just like the Al Capone case!

230
00:14:49,305 --> 00:14:52,391
Where the mafia boss was caught,
not because of the people he killed,

231
00:14:52,474 --> 00:14:54,810
but because of tax evasion!

232
00:14:54,894 --> 00:14:55,895
Exactly!

233
00:14:58,981 --> 00:15:01,025
It always leaves a trail behind.

234
00:15:11,535 --> 00:15:13,120
You think you're the only one? Me too.

235
00:15:13,203 --> 00:15:14,997
Me too! I love money as well.

236
00:15:18,542 --> 00:15:20,294
Cocoy, aside from your work at the agency,

237
00:15:20,377 --> 00:15:23,505
your job here is also
to keep an eye on Mikoy and Chiara.

238
00:15:25,215 --> 00:15:26,717
They seem to have a strange condition

239
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:28,844
that makes them want to
run away all the time.

240
00:15:45,194 --> 00:15:46,820
What time is she leaving?

241
00:15:46,904 --> 00:15:48,322
She didn't say.

242
00:15:48,948 --> 00:15:50,991
Mi amore, behave.

243
00:15:51,075 --> 00:15:54,244
She shouldn't feel
that you don't like her.

244
00:15:55,871 --> 00:15:57,831
But look at how she gives orders,

245
00:15:57,915 --> 00:16:00,542
it's like she has no plans
of ever leaving.

246
00:16:10,010 --> 00:16:10,844
Bianca!

247
00:16:13,889 --> 00:16:15,099
Can I ask you something?

248
00:16:50,843 --> 00:16:52,094
Hold on a second.

249
00:16:52,970 --> 00:16:54,388
Bianca.

250
00:16:55,180 --> 00:17:00,185
Boss, I heard she's staying here?

251
00:17:00,269 --> 00:17:04,732
Maybe I can stay here too,
so I can get more exposure.

252
00:17:09,653 --> 00:17:12,406
But the house is already
pretty close to here.

253
00:17:13,615 --> 00:17:14,950
Are you okay with walking?

254
00:17:15,701 --> 00:17:18,954
It's only about, 20 to 30 minutes away.

255
00:17:19,955 --> 00:17:20,831
That's close?

256
00:17:21,415 --> 00:17:22,916
Yes, it's not that far.

257
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:25,252
Just think of it as exercise.

258
00:17:26,503 --> 00:17:27,337
Is that okay?

259
00:17:29,339 --> 00:17:32,009
You know, haven't you noticed?

260
00:17:32,092 --> 00:17:36,263
Maybe this is the universe's way
of giving us some alone time.

261
00:17:36,346 --> 00:17:37,473
Just the two of us.

262
00:17:37,556 --> 00:17:39,308
Taking a walk together.

263
00:17:39,892 --> 00:17:41,518
Right? Can you imagine it?

264
00:17:41,602 --> 00:17:42,478
Fine.

265
00:17:42,978 --> 00:17:43,812
I agree.

266
00:17:44,938 --> 00:17:47,524
If you tell me the latest update
about my brother Mikoy.

267
00:17:47,608 --> 00:17:49,109
You thought I forgot?

268
00:17:49,193 --> 00:17:51,153
You said you still had
something to tell me.

269
00:17:53,197 --> 00:17:54,406
Angelito.

270
00:17:56,116 --> 00:17:57,493
I'll be honest with you.

271
00:17:58,327 --> 00:17:59,495
I'm sorry, but…

272
00:18:00,454 --> 00:18:02,081
I really don't know anything
about your brother.

273
00:18:02,164 --> 00:18:03,791
I have no updates.

274
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:07,169
But let me explain, okay?

275
00:18:07,252 --> 00:18:09,004
Okay, go ahead and explain.

276
00:18:09,088 --> 00:18:12,091
The thing is, you know that

277
00:18:12,174 --> 00:18:15,010
your brother's case is
pretty confidential.

278
00:18:15,636 --> 00:18:20,933
So, you know,
even Dad and the people at the agency,

279
00:18:21,016 --> 00:18:23,477
they don't tell me anything.

280
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:27,815
But I can assure you that
they're trying to save your brother,

281
00:18:27,898 --> 00:18:30,567
and they won't let anything happen to him.

282
00:18:30,651 --> 00:18:31,568
Yes.

283
00:18:52,172 --> 00:18:53,215
Sweetheart,

284
00:18:54,758 --> 00:18:56,510
what's his problem?

285
00:18:56,593 --> 00:18:58,303
Why does he keep staring?

286
00:18:58,971 --> 00:19:00,347
Who?

287
00:19:05,018 --> 00:19:06,186
You know, that's how it is

288
00:19:06,270 --> 00:19:09,439
when a bunch of strangers
start living in the same house.

289
00:19:10,941 --> 00:19:12,025
They observe each other.

290
00:19:13,986 --> 00:19:15,988
Checking each other out, you know?

291
00:19:16,071 --> 00:19:19,283
Figuring out your weaknesses
and your strengths.

292
00:19:19,366 --> 00:19:20,492
Oh, right.

293
00:19:20,576 --> 00:19:22,119
What do you want me to call you?

294
00:19:22,202 --> 00:19:25,205
I'm the Bisdak Heartthrob of Cebu.

295
00:19:26,081 --> 00:19:28,500
As for Cocoy, I think he's the

296
00:19:29,334 --> 00:19:31,295
Smart Buff of…

297
00:19:32,171 --> 00:19:33,213
wait, Cocoy!

298
00:19:33,881 --> 00:19:34,715
Where were you born?

299
00:19:34,798 --> 00:19:36,049
Guimaras. Why?

300
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:37,301
Nothing, thanks.

301
00:19:37,885 --> 00:19:42,139
Then Cocoy is the Smart Buff of Guimaras.

302
00:19:42,222 --> 00:19:43,599
See? What about you?

303
00:19:51,523 --> 00:19:53,317
The Pretty Femme Fatale of Prague?

304
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:54,693
There you go!

305
00:19:55,277 --> 00:19:56,904
Sweetheart, that suits you perfectly!

306
00:20:01,450 --> 00:20:03,660
And you? What do you want us to call you?

307
00:20:05,037 --> 00:20:06,496
Just call me Asian Cutie.

308
00:20:08,790 --> 00:20:10,083
That's a new one.

309
00:20:10,167 --> 00:20:11,293
Asian Cutie.

310
00:20:12,252 --> 00:20:13,754
Thanks for the reassurance.

311
00:20:15,047 --> 00:20:16,590
I needed that right now.

312
00:20:20,594 --> 00:20:23,555
You know, if what you're going through
is weighing heavily on you,

313
00:20:23,639 --> 00:20:25,015
you can share it with me.

314
00:20:26,683 --> 00:20:28,101
It's not that heavy.

315
00:20:29,770 --> 00:20:33,398
Mom and Dad are sharing
the burden of worrying about my brother.

316
00:20:34,024 --> 00:20:36,568
So, how are you two?

317
00:20:36,652 --> 00:20:37,527
Well,

318
00:20:39,279 --> 00:20:40,656
there hasn't been a single night

319
00:20:40,739 --> 00:20:43,116
that we haven't prayed
for Mikoy and Chiara.

320
00:20:43,700 --> 00:20:45,535
That they're safe and okay.

321
00:20:46,161 --> 00:20:48,789
I can't help but wonder,

322
00:20:48,872 --> 00:20:51,041
why did all of this have to happen?

323
00:20:52,501 --> 00:20:54,836
But at the same time,

324
00:20:55,879 --> 00:20:57,589
I understand.

325
00:20:58,548 --> 00:20:59,383
I mean,

326
00:21:00,884 --> 00:21:02,761
Mikoy loves Chiara.

327
00:21:04,471 --> 00:21:06,682
That's what love is like, huh?

328
00:21:07,557 --> 00:21:08,558
Oh, yes.

329
00:21:08,642 --> 00:21:10,227
You can say that again.

330
00:21:10,310 --> 00:21:11,144
Why?

331
00:21:11,812 --> 00:21:12,938
Have you never been in love?

332
00:21:14,523 --> 00:21:16,191
How did the topic end up on me?

333
00:21:16,775 --> 00:21:17,943
Nothing, it's just that, you know…

334
00:21:18,026 --> 00:21:18,860
I'm just curious about you,

335
00:21:18,944 --> 00:21:21,488
I still want to know more about you.

336
00:21:22,531 --> 00:21:26,076
So, were you mad at me when,

337
00:21:26,159 --> 00:21:28,287
you know, I lied?

338
00:21:29,663 --> 00:21:31,915
I already knew from the start that

339
00:21:31,999 --> 00:21:33,792
you were just making up stories
about your brother,

340
00:21:33,875 --> 00:21:35,544
that you didn't actually know anything.

341
00:21:35,627 --> 00:21:39,131
That's just part of who you are,
being playful.

342
00:21:39,214 --> 00:21:40,632
Being your Sofie self.

343
00:21:41,425 --> 00:21:42,509
If you're not playful,

344
00:21:43,844 --> 00:21:44,803
that's not you.

345
00:21:47,014 --> 00:21:48,765
You're really full of charm!

346
00:21:54,396 --> 00:21:55,272
You know what,

347
00:21:55,814 --> 00:21:57,316
let's commemorate,

348
00:21:57,399 --> 00:21:58,817
let's commemorate this day!

349
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:00,027
Let's take a photo!

350
00:22:01,028 --> 00:22:01,862
Of course, I'm ready.

351
00:22:02,446 --> 00:22:03,280
Here.

352
00:22:05,282 --> 00:22:06,450
Wait, wait, wait.

353
00:22:09,953 --> 00:22:12,664
There, this is perfect for posting.

354
00:22:14,291 --> 00:22:15,125
Wait,

355
00:22:16,209 --> 00:22:17,919
you've been taking pictures
for a while now,

356
00:22:18,003 --> 00:22:18,879
what's that for?

357
00:22:19,463 --> 00:22:23,008
I'm going to post this in my
"A Day in My Life" on Fishbook!

358
00:22:24,509 --> 00:22:25,343
Right?

359
00:22:25,427 --> 00:22:26,845
Wait, wait, wait.

360
00:22:26,928 --> 00:22:29,681
I just remembered a saying.

361
00:22:30,265 --> 00:22:32,976
That when a moment is perfect,

362
00:22:33,060 --> 00:22:37,898
it supposedly deserves a perfect kiss
when the 3Ps are complete.

363
00:22:39,816 --> 00:22:41,568
What are the 3Ps?

364
00:22:41,651 --> 00:22:42,819
You don't know that?

365
00:22:42,903 --> 00:22:44,946
- Listen carefully.
- Okay…

366
00:22:50,452 --> 00:22:51,870
Just like now.

367
00:22:58,668 --> 00:23:00,212
Um…

368
00:23:00,295 --> 00:23:02,547
What about the perfect person?

369
00:23:06,593 --> 00:23:07,969
Maybe, right?

370
00:23:20,941 --> 00:23:23,902
- You're just distracting yourself, huh?
- Yes!

371
00:23:23,985 --> 00:23:25,654
What else are we supposed
to do here, sweetheart?

372
00:23:25,737 --> 00:23:28,698
We need to adapt to our new environment.

373
00:23:28,782 --> 00:23:32,994
So I'll just wait around
for the next safe-mates to arrive here.

374
00:23:43,255 --> 00:23:44,673
Whatever that is,

375
00:23:45,257 --> 00:23:46,091
it ain't me.

376
00:23:46,967 --> 00:23:48,051
What are you doing?

377
00:23:48,135 --> 00:23:49,344
Why do you have a suitcase?

378
00:23:49,427 --> 00:23:51,346
This? It's not mine.

379
00:23:51,429 --> 00:23:52,556
It's Agent Alex's.

380
00:24:15,287 --> 00:24:16,371
Really?

381
00:24:22,252 --> 00:24:26,715
The alluring babysitter of G.A.G.O.

382
00:24:28,133 --> 00:24:30,343
Although we don't need a babysitter,

383
00:24:30,427 --> 00:24:33,972
because Cocoy is there to watch over us.

384
00:24:37,058 --> 00:24:39,311
Didn't you tell him a while ago?

385
00:24:42,314 --> 00:24:45,859
Hey, I'm still here in case you forgot.

386
00:24:47,027 --> 00:24:49,571
Actually Ben, you're out because of
what happened earlier.

387
00:24:56,244 --> 00:24:57,704
You're evicted already?!

388
00:24:57,787 --> 00:25:01,291
Come on! I didn't even give you a moniker.

389
00:25:04,169 --> 00:25:07,839
Agent Alex, here are the documents
that you asked me about earlier.

390
00:25:09,132 --> 00:25:10,425
Work already?

391
00:25:10,508 --> 00:25:12,219
You're such a workaholic.

392
00:25:19,434 --> 00:25:22,270
So I hope you two behave
while I'm working.

393
00:25:33,740 --> 00:25:35,825
I'm just replacing the bulbs.

394
00:25:36,409 --> 00:25:37,661
Let me help you.

395
00:25:37,744 --> 00:25:39,037
No, it's fine.

396
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:41,122
Uh, can you just turn it on?

397
00:25:41,206 --> 00:25:42,249
Hey, hey, hey! Hey!

398
00:26:08,441 --> 00:26:11,194
Why don't we raid the camp
of La Morte Bianca?

399
00:26:11,278 --> 00:26:15,365
Unfortunately, Chiara, here you'll
experience waiting and more hiding.

400
00:26:18,243 --> 00:26:21,162
We need to wait to
align with the law enforcement agency

401
00:26:21,246 --> 00:26:23,039
before we make a move.

402
00:26:23,123 --> 00:26:27,460
Otherwise, there might be a misencounter
with another police department,

403
00:26:27,544 --> 00:26:28,712
or even the military.

